		<title>There ARE Consequences</title>
		<link>http://betterdave.com/2007/11/01/53-there-are-consequences/</link>
		<comments>http://betterdave.com/2007/11/01/53-there-are-consequences/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Thu, 01 Nov 2007 21:40:28 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>dave@betterdave.com (David Jackson)</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Best Of]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Podcast]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Think]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Consequences]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Teenage Pregnancy]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://betterdave.com/2007/11/01/53-there-are-consequences/</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[The dumbing of America, Teen Pregnancy are now invading my life. I share my thoughts on the subject and what are possibly some of the reasons. Parents still bitter from a divorce want to prove the are the &#8220;cooler&#8221; parent and in the process throw their child under the bus. Children know that their parents [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p><font size="3"><img vspace="5" align="left" width="144" src="http://www.betterdave.com/images/consequences144.jpg" hspace="5" alt="Teenage Pregnancy" height="144" style="width: 144px; height: 144px" title="Teenage Pregnancy" />The dumbing of America, Teen Pregnancy are now invading my life. I share my thoughts on the subject and what are possibly some of the reasons.</font></p>
<p><font size="3">Parents still bitter from a divorce want to prove the are the &#8220;cooler&#8221; parent and in the process throw their child under the bus. </font></p>
<p><font size="3">Children know that their parents feel bad about the divorce and play on this guilt to get everything they want. I am entitled to this because you screwed up my life by divorcing my other parent. We end up with a society that thinks they get to do whatever they want. </font></p>
<p><font size="3">There are consequences. <strong>There</strong> <strong>ARE</strong> <strong>consequences</strong>. <em>Yes it is your fault</em>. No <strong>deal with it. </strong></font></p>
<p><font size="3">Quit using your kids as a weapon, and quit playing your parents against each other. </font></p>
<p><font size="3"><strong>MUSIC</strong><br />
